isValid

boolean isValid()
Tests if the license is valid. Validity logic is imposed by the license it self witch is free to implemented as it sees fit.

Returns:
true is the license is valid, false otherwise.

checkOut

void checkOut()
Allocates an instance of the license. Is not more instances are available a LicenceException is thrown

Throws:
InvalidLicenseException - if the license is invalid
NoMoreLicenseInstancesAvailableException - if no more instances are available at the moment
